<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - SPICER 13-INCH (310 MM) AND 14-INCH (350 MM) ANGLE-RING
        SINGLE PLATE PUSH-TYPE CLUTCH
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsection id="s11002" svcsectype="prodspec" division="truck" formnum="CTS-5057" date="03/01/1996">
        <title>SPICER 13-INCH (310 MM) AND 14-INCH (350 MM) ANGLE-RING SINGLE PLATE PUSH-TYPE CLUTCH</title>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <vendorgroup/>

                <vendor>Spicer</vendor>
                <ucodegroup/>

                <ucode>11265</ucode>
                <ucode>11266</ucode>
            </configure>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>1000</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>3000</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>4000</truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>The clutch installation consists of a clutch assembly and a driven disc assembly. The clutch
                    assembly is a levered, belleville spring design, and is bolted to the engine flywheel with Grade 8
                    capscrews.
                </para>
                <para>The pressure plate is driven by 3 drive straps that are attached to the flywheel ring.</para>
                <para>The driven disc assembly has ceramic friction pads, and a dampered (spring-loaded) center
                    section.
                </para>
                <para>Clutch and driven disc components are shown in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1100201">Figure 1</hotlnk>,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1100202">Figure 2</hotlnk>
                    and
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1100203">Figure 3</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1100201" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1100201" filename="../figg11/g1100201.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Push Type Clutch Assembly</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. CLUTCH LEVER</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f1100202" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1100202" filename="../figg11/g1100202.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2. 13 Inch (310 mm) Driven Disc Assembly</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. CERAMIC PAD</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f1100203" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1100203" filename="../figg11/g1100203.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3. 14 Inch (350 mm) Driven Disc Assembly</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. CERAMIC PAD</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
    </svcsection>
